I have been a paid member of Romeo (including under its previous names) for 10 years. Until recently, I have found it to be one of the better gay dating sites and I like that it one can still use it via a website and so a computer, and not just via an app. Unfortunately, when my current subscription expires, not only will I not be renewing the paid subscription but I will be deleting my profile. There are lots of minor reasons but collectively, Romeo is no longer a quality site / app. Examples: One can no longer search matches across the city but only radiating from the point where you are physically located. In a large city like London, this is really irritating because you are effectively restricted to guys local to you. It is a pain to try to search guys across the city. Despite paying for a premium membership, one only has 29 seconds to read a profile before the “hide your visit” button deactivates. Even paid members’ messages automatically delete after a week or so. Received messages can only be saved by manually saving each one. Sent messages cannot be saved at all. I mean, why?! The app is buggy and frequently doesn’t synchronize with what you have done (messages sent & received etc) on the website. Apart from the features getting steadily worse, the other reason I have decided to delete my profile is the poor support when you report a bug. I have been disappointed with the poor response from Romeo. There are a good number of decent guys on Romeo so it is a shame that Romeo’s site, app, and customer service have become so poor that they have lost a paying customer.
